source.description: Financial Industry Business Ontology (FIBO) - Full production RDF from EDM Council GitHub repository

BoardAgreement.name: BoardAgreement
BoardAgreement.description: formal, legally binding agreement between members of the Board of Directors of the organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

JointStockCompany.name: JointStockCompany
JointStockCompany.description: for-profit, unincorporated business that has some characteristics of a corporation and some features of a partnership, with ownership interests represented by shares of stock

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

PrivatelyHeldCompany.name: PrivatelyHeldCompany
PrivatelyHeldCompany.description: corporation whose issued shares are all held by a family or a small group of investors and, therefore, cannot be bought by the public

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

PubliclyHeldCompany.name: PubliclyHeldCompany
PubliclyHeldCompany.description: corporation whose shares are traded and held publicly

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

RegistrationIdentifier.name: RegistrationIdentifier
RegistrationIdentifier.description: identifier that is officially allocated to an organization at the time of registration, typically in a jurisdiction in which said organization is organized or registered and used in that jurisdiction to identify the organization

RegistrationIdentifierScheme.name: RegistrationIdentifierScheme
RegistrationIdentifierScheme.description: scheme that defines the registration identifier per the issuing registration authority

ReligiousCorporation.name: ReligiousCorporation
ReligiousCorporation.description: not-for-profit corporation whose objective is specific to some fundamental set of beliefs and practices generally agreed upon by a number of people, and that is incorporated under the law

BenefitCorporation.name: BenefitCorporation
BenefitCorporation.description: not-for-profit corporation set up under specific state legislation, typically to provide some social benefit, without an obligation to maximize shareholder return

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

CommonInterestDevelopmentCorporation.name: CommonInterestDevelopmentCorporation
CommonInterestDevelopmentCorporation.description: not-for-profit corporation set up under specific state legislation as a business entity for homeowners' associations

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Corporation.name: Corporation
Corporation.description: formal organization that is a legal entity (artificial person) distinct from its owners, created under the jurisdiction of the laws of a state or nation

ForProfitCorporation.name: ForProfitCorporation
ForProfitCorporation.description: corporation whose objective is to make money, i.e., to ensure realization of a financial benefit such that the amount of revenue gained from a business activity exceeds the expenses, costs and taxes needed to sustain that activity

IncorporationGuarantee.name: IncorporationGuarantee
IncorporationGuarantee.description: guarantee that is part of the financial basis by which some legal entity is incorporated

InstrumentOfIncorporation.name: InstrumentOfIncorporation
InstrumentOfIncorporation.description: memorandum and articles of association by which some legal entity is established

NotForProfitCorporation.name: NotForProfitCorporation
NotForProfitCorporation.description: corporation approved by its jurisdictional oversight and tax authorities as operating for educational, charitable, social, religious, civic or humanitarian purposes

Branch.name: Branch
Branch.description: part of a larger organization that might not be co-located with it

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Division.name: Division
Division.description: part of an organization, such as a line of business, that may have separate accounting and reporting requirements

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

JointVenture.name: JointVenture
JointVenture.description: legal entity that is formed between parties that pool their resources for the purpose of accomplishing a specific task but otherwise retain their distinct identities

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

NonGovernmentalOrganization.name: NonGovernmentalOrganization
NonGovernmentalOrganization.description: not-for-profit organization that functions independently of government

NotForProfitOrganization.name: NotForProfitOrganization
NotForProfitOrganization.description: organization that uses its surplus revenues to further achieve its purpose rather than distributing its surplus income to the organization's owners (directors, investors, and equivalents) as profit / dividends

OrganizationCoveringAgreement.name: OrganizationCoveringAgreement
OrganizationCoveringAgreement.description: contract between the principals in a formal organization that specifies the relationship between the principals, and between the principals and the entity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

TaxIdentifier.name: TaxIdentifier
TaxIdentifier.description: identifier assigned to a taxpayer that enables compulsory financial charges and other levies to be imposed on the taxpayer by a governmental organization in order to fund government spending and various public expenditures

BusinessEntity.name: BusinessEntity
BusinessEntity.description: entity that is formed and administered as per commercial law in order to engage in business activities

BusinessLicense.name: BusinessLicense
BusinessLicense.description: license that allows the holder to conduct business or carry out a specific profession within some jurisdiction for some period of time

CharteredLegalPerson.name: CharteredLegalPerson
CharteredLegalPerson.description: a legal person created by a royal charter or decree

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

LegallyCompetentNaturalPerson.name: LegallyCompetentNaturalPerson
LegallyCompetentNaturalPerson.description: person who is considered competent, under the circumstances, to enter into a contract, conduct business, or participate in other activities that generally require the mental ability to understand problems and make decisions on his or her own behalf

NotForProfitObjective.name: NotForProfitObjective
NotForProfitObjective.description: objective that reflects the charitable, educational, religious, humanitarian, public services, or other not for profit goals of an organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

PowerOfAttorney.name: PowerOfAttorney
PowerOfAttorney.description: legal authorization given by one party (the principal) to another (the agent or attorney-in-fact) to perform certain acts on the principal's behalf

ProfitObjective.name: ProfitObjective
ProfitObjective.description: objective that reflects pursuit of a financial benefit that may be realized when the amount of revenue gained from a business activity exceeds the expenses, costs and taxes needed to sustain that activity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

PublicPurpose.name: PublicPurpose
PublicPurpose.description: objective that reflects values generally thought to be shared by and that is intended to benefit the populace as a whole

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

ReligiousObjective.name: ReligiousObjective
ReligiousObjective.description: not-for-profit objective that reflects the religious goals of an organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: legal entity created to fulfill narrow, specific, and frequently temporary objectives

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

StatutoryBody.name: StatutoryBody
StatutoryBody.description: legal entity established by a government to consider evidence and make judgements in some field of activity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: legal entity whose shareholders are entitled to a percentage of a named company's profits via a private contract

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

AmountOfMoney.name: AmountOfMoney
AmountOfMoney.description: amount of readily available cash in banknotes and coins

CalculatedPrice.name: CalculatedPrice
CalculatedPrice.description: monetary price determined by a formula

Currency.name: Currency
Currency.description: medium of exchange value, defined by reference to the geographical location of the monetary authorities responsible for it

CurrencyBasket.name: CurrencyBasket
CurrencyBasket.description: selected group of currencies, in which the weighted average is used as a measure of the value or the amount of an obligation

CurrencyIdentifier.name: CurrencyIdentifier
CurrencyIdentifier.description: sequence of characters representing some currency

ExchangeRate.name: ExchangeRate
ExchangeRate.description: rate at which one currency can be exchanged for another

Funds.name: Funds
Funds.description: artificial currency used as calculation basis for another currency(s) and accounting purposes

FundsIdentifier.name: FundsIdentifier
FundsIdentifier.description: sequence of characters that can be used to uniquely identify funds

InterestRate.name: InterestRate
InterestRate.description: amount charged, expressed as a percentage of principal, in exchange for the use of assets

MonetaryAmount.name: MonetaryAmount
MonetaryAmount.description: measure that is an amount of money specified in monetary units

MonetaryPrice.name: MonetaryPrice
MonetaryPrice.description: price that that is expressed as a monetary amount

PercentageMonetaryAmount.name: PercentageMonetaryAmount
PercentageMonetaryAmount.description: measure of some amount of money expressed as a percentage of some other amount, some notional amount or some concrete money amount

PreciousMetalIdentifier.name: PreciousMetalIdentifier
PreciousMetalIdentifier.description: sequence of characters uniquely identifying the precious metal in some context

Price.name: Price
Price.description: amount of money, goods, or services requested, expected, required, or given in exchange for something else

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

UnitOfAccount.name: UnitOfAccount
UnitOfAccount.description: nominal monetary unit of measure used to represent the real value (or cost) of any economic item; i.e. goods, services, assets, liabilities, income, expenses

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

UnitOfAccountIdentifier.name: UnitOfAccountIdentifier
UnitOfAccountIdentifier.description: sequence of characters that can be used to uniquely identify a nominal monetary unit

UnitPrice.name: UnitPrice
UnitPrice.description: monetary price expressed in relation to a well-known measurable unit by which the goods or services are allocated

BusinessObjective.name: BusinessObjective
BusinessObjective.description: objective that reflects the strategic goals and direction of a business within a time frame and available resources

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

BusinessStrategy.name: BusinessStrategy
BusinessStrategy.description: strategy for achieving a specific business goal, objective, solution or outcome

DistributionStrategy.name: DistributionStrategy
DistributionStrategy.description: strategy for making a product or service available, or for distributing funds, such as in the form of a dividend or coupon

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

FinancialObjective.name: FinancialObjective
FinancialObjective.description: objective that reflects the strategic financial goals and direction of a party within a time frame and available resources

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Goal.name: Goal
Goal.description: desired result that a party envisions, plans, and to which it commits, in order to achieve a desired state

InvestmentObjective.name: InvestmentObjective
InvestmentObjective.description: financial objective used by an investor to determine whether or not a given potential investment is appropriate for themselves or on behalf of another party

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Objective.name: Objective
Objective.description: short-term, quantitative, measurable result that a party seeks to attain in order to achieve its long-term goals

Program.name: Program
Program.description: state of affairs and coordinated set of activities designed to obtain benefits not available from managing them individually

ProgramIdentifier.name: ProgramIdentifier
ProgramIdentifier.description: sequence of characters uniquely identifying a specific program within the context in which that program is administered

ProgramName.name: ProgramName
ProgramName.description: contextual designation for a program within the context in which that program is administered

Project.name: Project
Project.description: state of affairs and unique and temporary organization, designed to deliver a tangible output

ProjectIdentifier.name: ProjectIdentifier
ProjectIdentifier.description: sequence of characters uniquely identifying a specific project within the context in which that project or an overarching program is administered

SalesStrategy.name: SalesStrategy
SalesStrategy.description: strategy for selling something, including allocating resources to the sales process, reducing costs, and optimizing revenues

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Strategy.name: Strategy
Strategy.description: plan or method for achieving a specific goal, objective, solution or outcome

MaturityLevel.name: MaturityLevel
MaturityLevel.description: classifier used to indicate the state of an artifact with respect to its development lifecycle

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Module.name: Module
Module.description: classifier used to indicate a category used to modularize something based on principles of the model driven architecture methodology (MDA), including but not limited to separation of concerns, coherence, and establishing clear logical boundaries in order to increase reusability and maintainability

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Association.name: Association
Association.description: not-for-profit organization that is owned by and acts on behalf of its members

CooperativeSociety.name: CooperativeSociety
CooperativeSociety.description: organization owned by and operated for the benefit of those using its services

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

FamilyOffice.name: FamilyOffice
FamilyOffice.description: organization that assumes the day-to-day administration and management of a family's affairs

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

FunctionalBusinessEntity.name: FunctionalBusinessEntity
FunctionalBusinessEntity.description: functional entity defined in terms of the nature of the commercial activity it conducts

FunctionalEntity.name: FunctionalEntity
FunctionalEntity.description: party defined in terms of a function it performs

Merchant.name: Merchant
Merchant.description: party engaged in the purchase and sales of goods produced by others for profit

MerchantCategoryCode.name: MerchantCategoryCode
MerchantCategoryCode.description: code used internationally to classify a merchant

MerchantCategoryCodeScheme.name: MerchantCategoryCodeScheme
MerchantCategoryCodeScheme.description: scheme defining a set of codes for classifying merchant services

MerchantIdentifier.name: MerchantIdentifier
MerchantIdentifier.description: unique identifier for a merchant that is used, for example, for transaction interchange purposes

description._: temporary, self-organizing group of people, companies, corporations or entities organized as an alliance whose purpose is to transact some specific business, or to pursue or promote a shared interest
role of an individual or organization that is a member of an alliance set up to pool resources and share risk with respect to a large transaction

OrganizationIdentifier.name: OrganizationIdentifier
OrganizationIdentifier.description: OrganizationIdentifier as defined in OWL ontology

IndustrySectorClassificationScheme.name: IndustrySectorClassificationScheme
IndustrySectorClassificationScheme.description: system for allocating classifiers to organizations by industry sector

IndustrySectorClassifier.name: IndustrySectorClassifier
IndustrySectorClassifier.description: standardized classification or delineation for an organization, or possibly for a security representing an interest in a given organization, per some scheme for such delineation, by industry

Referent.name: Referent
Referent.description: something that another concept stands for, exemplifies, symbolizes, or otherwise mentions

MarketDataProvider.name: MarketDataProvider
MarketDataProvider.description: publisher of data relevant to financial markets

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Publication.name: Publication
Publication.description: document offered for general distribution and usually produced in multiple copies

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Publisher.name: Publisher
Publisher.description: role of person(s) or organization(s) responsible for the printing or distribution of an item, whether in digital or print (physical) form

BranchOfGovernment.name: BranchOfGovernment
BranchOfGovernment.description: division of the government of a state, with separate and independent powers and areas of responsibility so that the powers of one branch are not in conflict with the powers associated with the other branches

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

DevolvedGovernment.name: DevolvedGovernment
DevolvedGovernment.description: government and the politicians that that run a subnational territory with powers that may be temporary and reversible, ultimately residing with the central government

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

ExecutiveBranch.name: ExecutiveBranch
ExecutiveBranch.description: the branch of government that is authorized and responsible for the daily administration of the government

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

FederalGovernment.name: FederalGovernment
FederalGovernment.description: union of states under a central government distinct from the individual governments of the separate states

FederatedSovereignty.name: FederatedSovereignty
FederatedSovereignty.description: polity characterized by a union of partially self-governing states or regions under a central (federal) government

Government.name: Government
Government.description: the system by which a state or community is controlled

GovernmentAgency.name: GovernmentAgency
GovernmentAgency.description: permanent or semi-permanent organization, often an appointed commission, in the machinery of government that is responsible for the oversight and administration of specific functions

GovernmentAppointee.name: GovernmentAppointee
GovernmentAppointee.description: individual designated by government decree to lead, or participate in some capacity in a government body

GovernmentBody.name: GovernmentBody
GovernmentBody.description: formal organization that is an agency, instrumentality, or other body of a supranational, national, federal, state, or local government, including certain multijurisdictional agencies and departments that carry out the business of government

GovernmentDepartment.name: GovernmentDepartment
GovernmentDepartment.description: specialized organization responsible for a sector of government public administration

GovernmentMinister.name: GovernmentMinister
GovernmentMinister.description: government official that is an executive, who is either appointed or elected to a high office in the government

GovernmentOfficial.name: GovernmentOfficial
GovernmentOfficial.description: person elected or appointed to administer some aspect of a government

Instrumentality.name: Instrumentality
Instrumentality.description: organization that serves a public purpose and is closely tied to a government, but is not a government agency

Judiciary.name: Judiciary
Judiciary.description: branch of government that comprises the system of courts that interprets and applies the law in the name of the supranational, national, federal, or regional government, depending on its jurisdiction

Legislature.name: Legislature
Legislature.description: the law-making body of a political unit, usually a national government, that has power to enact, amend, and repeal public policy

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

MunicipalEntity.name: MunicipalEntity
MunicipalEntity.description: polity that typically represents a city, township, or other administrative subdivision having corporate status and powers of self-government or jurisdiction

MunicipalGovernment.name: MunicipalGovernment
MunicipalGovernment.description: regional government of a city, township, or other administrative subdivision

NationalGovernment.name: NationalGovernment
NationalGovernment.description: government and the politicians that that run a country as a whole (as opposed to local government)

Polity.name: Polity
Polity.description: legal person that is a supranational entity, crown, state, or subordinate civil authority, such as a province, prefecture, county, municipality, city, or district representing the people of that entity

RegionalGovernment.name: RegionalGovernment
RegionalGovernment.description: administrative body for a geographic area, such as a county, smaller town, or other similar community

RegionalSovereignty.name: RegionalSovereignty
RegionalSovereignty.description: legal person that corresponds to an administrative division, administrative unit, administrative entity or country subdivision (or, sometimes, geopolitical division or subnational entity), that has the capacity to incur debt, issue contracts, and enter into relations with other similar entities

SovereignState.name: SovereignState
SovereignState.description: non-physical juridical entity that is represented by one centralized government that has sovereignty over a geographic area

SupranationalEntity.name: SupranationalEntity
SupranationalEntity.description: governmental or non-governmental entity that is established by international law or treaty or incorporated at an international level

TribalArea.name: TribalArea
TribalArea.description: designation for geographic region administered by a group of indigenous people rather than by a sovereign state or regional governmental entity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

TribalEntity.name: TribalEntity
TribalEntity.description: legal entity that represents fundamental unit of sovereign tribal (indigenous) government

TribalGovernment.name: TribalGovernment
TribalGovernment.description: government representing a group of indigenous people that has legal authority to govern those people, including authority to legislate the existence of tribal entities

NationalIdentificationNumber.name: NationalIdentificationNumber
NationalIdentificationNumber.description: number or text which appears on an identity document issued by a country or jurisdiction

VotingShareholder.name: VotingShareholder
VotingShareholder.description: shareholder whose shares confer the right to vote in corporate elections, including the right to elect directors at annual or special meetings, and to express their views to corporate management and directors on significant issues that may affect the value of those shares

ArticlesOfIncorporation.name: ArticlesOfIncorporation
ArticlesOfIncorporation.description: contract that establishes a new corporation or, when amended, adjusts the legal basis for the corporation, and outlines basic information about the corporation, including the type of business, and a description of the business' operational characteristics

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Auditor.name: Auditor
Auditor.description: party qualified and authorized to review and verify the accuracy of financial records and ensure that companies comply with tax laws

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Authorization.name: Authorization
Authorization.description: situation in which a party authorizes someone to act on their behalf under certain conditions for some period of time

AuthorizedParty.name: AuthorizedParty
AuthorizedParty.description: party that has been given the responsibility to act on behalf of another party under some set of guidelines

AuthorizingParty.name: AuthorizingParty
AuthorizingParty.description: party that delegates some role, authority, or control to another party

BoardCapacity.name: BoardCapacity
BoardCapacity.description: authority to act in a fiduciary capacity with respect to the organization, including but not limited to determining and executing corporate policy

BoardCompositionControl.name: BoardCompositionControl
BoardCompositionControl.description: situation in which a voting shareholder, entity owner, or some other party in the case of a not-for-profit organization, appoints and/or nominates someone to the board of directors of an organization for some period of time

BoardMember.name: BoardMember
BoardMember.description: party that has fiduciary responsibility with respect to the organization, including but not limited to determining and executing corporate policy

BoardMembership.name: BoardMembership
BoardMembership.description: situation relating an individual member of the board of directors to the organization

BoardOfDirectors.name: BoardOfDirectors
BoardOfDirectors.description: group of people comprising the governing body of an organization that has the authority to set organizational strategy and policies as well as to select and, to some degree manage, leadership

Bylaws.name: Bylaws
Bylaws.description: written rules for conduct of a corporation, association, partnership or any organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

ChiefExecutiveOfficer.name: ChiefExecutiveOfficer
ChiefExecutiveOfficer.description: top corporate officer responsible for an organization's overall operations and performance

ChiefFinancialOfficer.name: ChiefFinancialOfficer
ChiefFinancialOfficer.description: senior-most corporate officer responsible for financial control and planning for an organization or project

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

CompanyLaw.name: CompanyLaw
CompanyLaw.description: legislation under which the formation, registration or incorporation, governance, and dissolution of a firm is administered and controlled

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

CompanySecretary.name: CompanySecretary
CompanySecretary.description: corporate officer appointed by the directors of an organization, responsible for ensuring compliance with legal obligations related to corporate governance

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

CorporateBylaws.name: CorporateBylaws
CorporateBylaws.description: written rules for conduct of a corporation, adopted by the board of directors

CorporateOfficer.name: CorporateOfficer
CorporateOfficer.description: high-level management executive of a corporation or other organization, hired by the board of directors or the business owner(s), charged with certain operational responsibilities, and who has the authority to act on behalf of the organization, including the authority to enter into contracts on behalf of the organization

Executive.name: Executive
Executive.description: person appointed and given the responsibility to manage the affairs of an organization and the authority to make decisions within specified role-specific boundaries

ExecutiveBoardMember.name: ExecutiveBoardMember
ExecutiveBoardMember.description: member of a board of directors that is also an employee of the organization

LegallyDelegatedAuthority.name: LegallyDelegatedAuthority
LegallyDelegatedAuthority.description: party empowered with some level of legal control and corresponding responsibility

NonExecutiveBoardMember.name: NonExecutiveBoardMember
NonExecutiveBoardMember.description: member of the board of directors of an organization that has no executive responsibilities towards the running of that organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

PrincipalParty.name: PrincipalParty
PrincipalParty.description: controlling party that is responsible for the management of daily business operations of an organization

ResponsibleParty.name: ResponsibleParty
ResponsibleParty.description: person acting in a role that has some formal responsibility, such as a fiduciary responsibility, a signatory, an examiner or registrar, etc.

Signatory.name: Signatory
Signatory.description: responsible party authorized to sign agreements on behalf of themselves, another person, or an organization

Adult.name: Adult
Adult.description: person who has attained the age of majority as defined in some jurisdiction

AgeOfMajority.name: AgeOfMajority
AgeOfMajority.description: age at which someone acquires the rights and responsibilities of an adult in some jurisdiction

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

BirthCertificateIdentificationScheme.name: BirthCertificateIdentificationScheme
BirthCertificateIdentificationScheme.description: system for allocating identifiers to birth certificates

BirthCertificateIdentifier.name: BirthCertificateIdentifier
BirthCertificateIdentifier.description: identifier associated with a vital record documenting the birth of a child

DateOfBirth.name: DateOfBirth
DateOfBirth.description: explicit date, i.e., the day, month and year, on which an individual was born

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

DateOfDeath.name: DateOfDeath
DateOfDeath.description: explicit date, i.e., the day, month and year, on which an individual died

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

DeathCertificateIdentificationScheme.name: DeathCertificateIdentificationScheme
DeathCertificateIdentificationScheme.description: system for allocating identifiers to death certificates

DeathCertificateIdentifier.name: DeathCertificateIdentifier
DeathCertificateIdentifier.description: identifier associated with a vital record documenting the death of an individual

DriversLicense.name: DriversLicense
DriversLicense.description: an official document which states that a person may operate a motorized vehicle, such as a motorcycle, car, truck or a bus, on a public roadway or provides official identifying information for a non-driver

DriversLicenseIdentificationScheme.name: DriversLicenseIdentificationScheme
DriversLicenseIdentificationScheme.description: system for allocating identifiers to driver's, operating, or non-driver identification documents

DriversLicenseIdentifier.name: DriversLicenseIdentifier
DriversLicenseIdentifier.description: identifier associated with a drivers' or operating license for operating a motor vehicle or non-driver identification card

EmancipatedMinor.name: EmancipatedMinor
EmancipatedMinor.description: a minor who is allowed to conduct a business or any other occupation on his or her own behalf or for their own account outside the control of a parent or guardian

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

IncapacitatedAdult.name: IncapacitatedAdult
IncapacitatedAdult.description: an adult who is legally identified as not having legal capacity, typically as a result of some inherent physical or mental incapacity or as a result of having contracted some illness which temporarily deprives them of such capacity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

LegalAge.name: LegalAge
LegalAge.description: age at which someone acquires the capacity to do something that they were prohibited from doing before under the law in some jurisdiction

LegalWorkingAge.name: LegalWorkingAge
LegalWorkingAge.description: age at which someone acquires the capacity to work legally in some jurisdiction

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

LegalWorkingAgePerson.name: LegalWorkingAgePerson
LegalWorkingAgePerson.description: person whose age is greater than the minimum legal working age specified in a jurisdiction in which they work

LegallyCapableAdult.name: LegallyCapableAdult
LegallyCapableAdult.description: person who has attained the age of majority as defined in some jurisdiction and who is allowed to conduct a business or any other occupation on his or her own behalf or for their own account

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Minor.name: Minor
Minor.description: a person under a certain age, usually the age of majority in a given jurisdiction, which legally demarcates childhood from adulthood

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

NationalIdentificationNumberScheme.name: NationalIdentificationNumberScheme
NationalIdentificationNumberScheme.description: system for allocating identifiers to national identification numbers

Passport.name: Passport
Passport.description: formal identity document, issued by a national government, which certifies the identity and nationality of its holder for the purpose of international travel

PassportNumber.name: PassportNumber
PassportNumber.description: national identification number associated with a passport

PassportNumberIdentificationScheme.name: PassportNumberIdentificationScheme
PassportNumberIdentificationScheme.description: system for allocating identifiers to passports

Person.name: Person
Person.description: individual human being, with consciousness of self

PersonName.name: PersonName
PersonName.description: designation by which someone is known in some context

PlaceOfBirth.name: PlaceOfBirth
PlaceOfBirth.description: physical location, including country, region, and municipality where an individual was born

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Constitution.name: Constitution
Constitution.description: set of basic principles by which an organization is governed, especially in relation to the rights of the people it governs

CourtOfLaw.name: CourtOfLaw
CourtOfLaw.description: person or body of persons having judicial authority to hear and resolve disputes on the basis of statutes or the common law

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

Law.name: Law
Law.description: rule recognized by some community as regulating the behavior of its members and that it may enforce through the imposition of penalties

CapitalSurplus.name: CapitalSurplus
CapitalSurplus.description: capital contributed in excess of the par value (stated value) of the ownership interest issued

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

EarningsBeforeInterestTaxesDepreciationA.name: EarningsBeforeInterestTaxesDepreciationAmortization
EarningsBeforeInterestTaxesDepreciationA.description: measure of potential cash flow that excludes the effects of capital structure, taxes and non-cash expenses

Income.name: Income
Income.description: revenue received during a period of time

OwnersEquity.name: OwnersEquity
OwnersEquity.description: owners' share in a business plus operating profit

PaidInCapital.name: PaidInCapital
PaidInCapital.description: assets received from investors in exchange for an ownership interest

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

PhysicalAsset.name: PhysicalAsset
PhysicalAsset.description: tangible asset that has a material form, such as property, equipment, and inventory

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

RetainedEarnings.name: RetainedEarnings
RetainedEarnings.description: net profits kept to accumulate in a business after dividends are paid

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: equity that is manifested in the form of shares in an entity, fund or structured product

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

AssignableContract.name: AssignableContract
AssignableContract.description: contract in which contract holder (assignor) may transfer some or all of their rights and obligations to another party (assignee)

BilateralContract.name: BilateralContract
BilateralContract.description: contract where two parties commit to perform specific actions or obligations towards each other

description._: netting provision that occurs between two parties, in which mutual obligations are offset to determine a single net payment
classifier of events representing a violation of an express, or implied, condition of a contract to do or not to do something, without a legitimate excuse
classifier of events representing breaking a promise specified in a contract to do or not to do something, without a legitimate excuse
netting provision that may be triggered when a counterparty defaults, leading to the termination of all outstanding transactions between the parties

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

CollateralAgreement.name: CollateralAgreement
CollateralAgreement.description: written contract related to another contract designed to provide clarity and additional protection for all parties involved, that is separate from the primary contract and that can be independently enforced

Contract.name: Contract
Contract.description: voluntary, deliberate agreement between competent parties to which the parties agree to be legally bound, and for which the parties provide valuable consideration

ContractDocument.name: ContractDocument
ContractDocument.description: legal document that records the formal terms and conditions of some contract

description._: classifier for an event (milestone), or set of events related to the status or level of completion of a designated activity, task, or segment of work required for contract fulfillment

ContractParty.name: ContractParty
ContractParty.description: legally competent party that has entered into a binding agreement, accepting and conceding obligations, responsibilities, and benefits as specified

ContractPrincipal.name: ContractPrincipal
ContractPrincipal.description: party that originates a contract and is identified as the first party to that contract, in the event that the contract distinguishes any party as such

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

ContractThirdParty.name: ContractThirdParty
ContractThirdParty.description: party that is indirectly involved in, but not a counterparty to, an agreement

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

ContractualCommitment.name: ContractualCommitment

AverageMonthlyEarnings.name: AverageMonthlyEarnings

AverageWeeklyEarnings.name: AverageWeeklyEarnings
AverageWeeklyEarnings.description: measure of the average weekly wage an employee makes over the reporting period

CivilianLaborForce.name: CivilianLaborForce

EmployedPopulationPartTimeForEconomicRea.description: subset of the employed population that includes persons that are working fewer than 30 to 35 hours per week due to slack work, unfavorable business conditions, inability to find full-time work, and seasonal declines in demand

EmployedPopulationPartTimeForNonEconomic.name: EmployedPopulationPartTimeForNonEconomicReasons

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

EmployedPopulationTemporarilyNotAtWork.name: EmployedPopulationTemporarilyNotAtWork
EmployedPopulationTemporarilyNotAtWork.description: subset of the employed population that includes persons that are temporarily absent from work for various reasons

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

EmploymentPopulationRatio.name: EmploymentPopulationRatio
EmploymentPopulationRatio.description: economic indicator representing the ratio of the employed population with respect to the overall civilian non-institutional population of a given economy for some specified period

Enterprise.name: Enterprise

EnterprisePopulation.name: EnterprisePopulation

Establishment.name: Establishment
Establishment.description: an enterprise (or part of an enterprise) that operates from a single physical location

FixedBasket.name: FixedBasket

HousingUnit.name: HousingUnit

InflationRate.name: InflationRate

InputProducerPriceIndex.name: InputProducerPriceIndex
InputProducerPriceIndex.description: economic indicator representing measure of the rate of change over time in the prices of inputs of goods and services purchased by the producer

InstitutionalPerson.name: InstitutionalPerson

InstitutionalUnit.name: InstitutionalUnit
InstitutionalUnit.description: party that is capable, in its own right, of owning assets, incurring liabilities, and engaging in economic activities and in transactions with other parties

LaborProductivityGrossOutput.name: LaborProductivityGrossOutput
LaborProductivityGrossOutput.description: ratio of a quantity index of gross output to a quantity index of labor input

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

LaborProductivityValueAdded.name: LaborProductivityValueAdded
LaborProductivityValueAdded.description: ratio of a quantity index of value added to a quantity index of labor input

MicropolitanStatisticalArea.name: MicropolitanStatisticalArea
MicropolitanStatisticalArea.description: one or more adjacent counties or county equivalents that have at least one urban core area of at least 10,000 population but less than 50,000, plus adjacent territory that has a high degree of social and economic integration with the core as measured by commuting ties

MilitaryPerson.name: MilitaryPerson

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

OutputProducerPriceIndex.name: OutputProducerPriceIndex
OutputProducerPriceIndex.description: economic indicator representing measure of the rate of change over time in the prices of products sold as they leave the producer

PersonalConsumptionExpenditures.description: economic indicator representing measure of the value of the goods and services purchased by, or on the behalf of, 'persons'

PopulationNotInLaborForce.name: PopulationNotInLaborForce
PopulationNotInLaborForce.description: subset of the civilian, noninstitutional population, that is considered neither employed nor unemployed by the reporting agency during the reporting period

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

ProducerPriceIndex.name: ProducerPriceIndex
ProducerPriceIndex.description: economic indicator representing measure of the rate of change over time in the prices of goods and services bought and sold by producers

Productivity.name: Productivity
Productivity.description: economic indicator representing ratio of a volume measure of output to a volume measure of input use

StatisticalInformationPublisher.name: StatisticalInformationPublisher
StatisticalInformationPublisher.description: publisher that packages and makes analytical and statistical data available

UltimateConsumer.name: UltimateConsumer
UltimateConsumer.description: person that is the ultimate user of a good, product or service

UnderemployedPopulation.name: UnderemployedPopulation
UnderemployedPopulation.description: subset of the employed population that includes persons employed part-time for economic reasons, who want and are available for full-time work but have had to settle for a part-time schedule

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

UnderemployedPopulationWithRespectToOccu.name: UnderemployedPopulationWithRespectToOccupation
UnderemployedPopulationWithRespectToOccu.description: subset of the underemployed population that includes persons employed in a role that does not reflect their training and experience, excluding those that change careers

PriceVolatility.name: PriceVolatility
PriceVolatility.description: statistical measure of the rate of change in pricing for a given security or market index

QuotedPrice.name: QuotedPrice
QuotedPrice.description: a monetary price quoted by some publisher on a given date

TermStructure.name: TermStructure
TermStructure.description: structured collection of rates, such as interest rates, or bond yields with different terms to maturity, such that a yield curve may be constructed for the structure

Volatility.name: Volatility

hasNotificationProvision.name: hasNotificationProvision
hasNotificationProvision.description: relates the redemption provision of a debt instrument to a notification provision (e.g., call or put notification)

hasPriceAndYieldDayCountConvention.name: hasPriceAndYieldDayCountConvention
hasPriceAndYieldDayCountConvention.description: indicates the convention used to determine the number of days in a month and days in a year that are counted when performing calculations for yield and price figures

hasPutFeature.name: hasPutFeature
hasPutFeature.description: indicates the specific terms related to any inherent put feature as specified in the offering/instrument

hasRelativePriceAtIssue.name: hasRelativePriceAtIssue
hasRelativePriceAtIssue.description: indicates a relative price with respect to the face value at which an instrument is issued, namely par, premium or discount

hasRelativePriceAtMaturity.name: hasRelativePriceAtMaturity
hasRelativePriceAtMaturity.description: indicates a relative price with respect to the face value at the time an instrument matures, namely par, discount or premium

hasRelativePriceAtRedemption.name: hasRelativePriceAtRedemption
hasRelativePriceAtRedemption.description: indicates a relative price with respect to the face value at the time an instrument is redeemed, namely par, discount or premium

hasRepaymentTerms.name: hasRepaymentTerms
hasRepaymentTerms.description: indicates the specific terms related to repayment of principal as specified in the instrument or a related contract document

isSubordinatedTo.name: isSubordinatedTo
isSubordinatedTo.description: indicates the target security (i.e., the one in the range) has a higher priority than the security in question

description._: grants ownership via contract

hasAdjustableDividendRate.name: hasAdjustableDividendRate
hasAdjustableDividendRate.description: indicates a variable dividend rate, typically specified in the prospectus as a formula based on a benchmark or set at auction

hasDistributionMethod.name: hasDistributionMethod
hasDistributionMethod.description: indicates the method by which dividend payments are to be distributed

hasDividend.name: hasDividend
hasDividend.description: relates a share to a dividend that applies to that share, or that the share may pay

hasDividendDeclarationDate.name: hasDividendDeclarationDate
hasDividendDeclarationDate.description: indicates a date on which an organization states that a dividend payment may be anticipated, including the the dividend amount and the ex-dividend and payment dates

hasDividendGracePeriod.name: hasDividendGracePeriod
hasDividendGracePeriod.description: indicates a period of time after a dividend payment becomes due, before the issuer is subject to penalties

hasEarliestRedemptionDate.name: hasEarliestRedemptionDate
hasEarliestRedemptionDate.description: indicates a date on or after which a stock can be redeemed

hasExDividendDate.name: hasExDividendDate
hasExDividendDate.description: indicates a date on which a stock 'goes ex-dividend', typically about three weeks before the dividend is paid to shareholders of record

hasFixedDividendRate.name: hasFixedDividendRate
hasFixedDividendRate.description: indicates a pre-arranged fixed dividend rate, typically specified in the prospectus, for a preferred share

hasMinimumRedemptionPrice.name: hasMinimumRedemptionPrice
hasMinimumRedemptionPrice.description: indicates the lowest market price above which a share may be redeemed

hasRecordDate.name: hasRecordDate
hasRecordDate.description: indicates the date on which the issuer checks to determine whether a party was on the company's books as a shareholder when required (i.e., they must have been on the books prior to the ex-dividend date), to identify who is eligible to receive the next dividend

hasRedemptionPremium.name: hasRedemptionPremium
hasRedemptionPremium.description: indicates the premium price per share over the market price, if any, that must be paid in order to redeem the stock

description._: indicates the payment status for shares issued

isSeniorTo.name: isSeniorTo
isSeniorTo.description: indicates that a given share (share class) has higher seniority than the related share, meaning that it gives the holder a higher claim on the assets of the issuer

specifiesConversionDate.name: specifiesConversionDate
specifiesConversionDate.description: indicates the date on which, or after which, conversion may occur

hasActualClosingDate.name: hasActualClosingDate
hasActualClosingDate.description: indicates the date on which an offering or transaction officially closes, in contrast with an intended closing date

hasAnnouncementDate.name: hasAnnouncementDate
hasAnnouncementDate.description: indicates the first day the public will receive information regarding a new security issue

hasFinancialInstrumentShortName.name: hasFinancialInstrumentShortName
hasFinancialInstrumentShortName.description: relates a security to its ISO 18774-compliant short name, which includes an issuer short name, abbreviated instrument characteristics, and abbreviated instrument description per the ISO standard

hasFirstTradeDate.name: hasFirstTradeDate
hasFirstTradeDate.description: indicates the date on which a newly issued security starts trading

hasFirstTradeSettlementDate.name: hasFirstTradeSettlementDate
hasFirstTradeSettlementDate.description: indicates the date on which the first trade of a newly issued security is settled

hasSubscriptionPeriod.name: hasSubscriptionPeriod
hasSubscriptionPeriod.description: indicates a period of time in which investors can commit to purchase shares (or units) to be issued

isIssuedInForm.name: isIssuedInForm
isIssuedInForm.description: indicates the form in which the security is issued, typically in registered form

isRegisteredWith.name: isRegisteredWith
isRegisteredWith.description: indicates the registration authority for a given security, i.e., in the name of the owner on the books of the issuer, with the issuer's registrar, with a third-party transfer agent, with a broker-dealer, or other competent party

isUnderwrittenBy.name: isUnderwrittenBy
isUnderwrittenBy.description: relates an offering to an underwriter involved in raising capital for or distributing the instruments that are the subject of the offering

specifiesConversionInto.name: specifiesConversionInto
specifiesConversionInto.description: specifies a security that will replace a convertible security under the terms of the agreement

underwrites.name: underwrites
underwrites.description: identifies one or more underwriters involved in raising capital for or distributing the instruments that are the subject of the offering

hasAttachmentPoint.name: hasAttachmentPoint
hasAttachmentPoint.description: indicates the minimum (lower boundary) of the total value of the underlying collateral, either at issuance or as of some point in time, at which point a given tranche becomes liable for losses

hasDetachmentPoint.name: hasDetachmentPoint
hasDetachmentPoint.description: indicates the maximum (upper boundary) of the total value of the underlying collateral, either at issuance or as of some point in time, at which point the value of given tranche is wiped out

hasEstimatedTotalCollateralValueAtIssuan.name: hasEstimatedTotalCollateralValueAtIssuance
hasEstimatedTotalCollateralValueAtIssuan.description: indicates the estimated value of the combined underlying collateral for a given tranche at the time the instrument was issued

hasEntityExpirationReason.name: hasEntityExpirationReason
hasEntityExpirationReason.description: indicates the reason that an entity ceased to exist (i.e., disolved, merged with another entity, etc.)

hasEntityStatus.name: hasEntityStatus
hasEntityStatus.description: indicates the status of the entity (i.e., active, inactive)

hasRegistrationStatus.name: hasRegistrationStatus
hasRegistrationStatus.description: indicates the status of a specific registration, such as for an identifier or license

hasValidationAuthority.name: hasValidationAuthority
hasValidationAuthority.description: identifies the business registration authority for the legal entity, used by the Local Operating Unit (LOU) as the basis for validation, as defined in the GLEIF Registration Authorities List

hasValidationLevel.name: hasValidationLevel
hasValidationLevel.description: indicates the level of validation performed by the registrar with respect to the legal entity

hasPrimaryFederalRegulator.name: hasPrimaryFederalRegulator
hasPrimaryFederalRegulator.description: identifies the primary federal regulator for an institution

hasSecondaryFederalRegulator.name: hasSecondaryFederalRegulator
hasSecondaryFederalRegulator.description: identifies an additional federal regulator, over and above the primary federal regulator, for an institution

hasFirstNotionalStepDate.name: hasFirstNotionalStepDate
hasFirstNotionalStepDate.description: indicates the initial date in a notional step schedule

hasFloatingRateCap.name: hasFloatingRateCap
hasFloatingRateCap.description: indicates an optional ceiling (cap) on interest rates on floating rate debts

hasFloatingRateFloor.name: hasFloatingRateFloor
hasFloatingRateFloor.description: indicates an optional lower bound on interest rates on floating rate debts

hasLastNotionalStepDate.name: hasLastNotionalStepDate
hasLastNotionalStepDate.description: indicates the final date in a notional step schedule

hasBusinessDayConvention.name: hasBusinessDayConvention
hasBusinessDayConvention.description: identifies a convention regarding how a date should be handled when it falls on a day that is not a business day, such as a weekend or holiday

hasBusinessRecurrenceIntervalConvention.name: hasBusinessRecurrenceIntervalConvention
hasBusinessRecurrenceIntervalConvention.description: identifies a convention regarding how certain recurring dates should be handled with respect to a given schedule, such as the end of the month

hasAcquisitionPrice.name: hasAcquisitionPrice
hasAcquisitionPrice.description: has a value as of the date of acquisition, expressed as an amount of money or goods

hasGuaranteedAmount.name: hasGuaranteedAmount
hasGuaranteedAmount.description: relates the guaranty to the monetary amount guaranteed

hasGuarantor.name: hasGuarantor
hasGuarantor.description: relates the guarantor to the contract for which they are providing a guaranty

hasGuarantorParty.name: hasGuarantorParty
hasGuarantorParty.description: indicates a party that guarantees, endorses, or provides indemnity for some obligation on its behalf

hasPriorityLevel.name: hasPriorityLevel
hasPriorityLevel.description: relates a guaranty to some relative ranking that the guaranty has in the context of the contract, for example for a credit enhancement priority

isGuaranteedBy.name: isGuaranteedBy
isGuaranteedBy.description: relates guaranty to the contract guarantor, i.e., to the legal person providing the guaranty

isGuarantorOf.name: isGuarantorOf
isGuarantorOf.description: identifies a party over which a guarantor has some measure of control by virtue of the guarantee

isIndexTo.name: isIndexTo
isIndexTo.description: that to which the index refers

description._: date on which a report was issued
date and time at which a report was issued
date on which a request was made
date and time at which a request was made

isReportedTo.name: isReportedTo
isReportedTo.description: indicates the party to which something is reported

isRequestedBy.name: isRequestedBy
isRequestedBy.description: indicates the party that asks for something

isRequestedOf.name: isRequestedOf
isRequestedOf.description: indicates the party that is asked for something

isSubmittedBy.name: isSubmittedBy
isSubmittedBy.description: indicates the party that submits something

isSubmittedTo.name: isSubmittedTo
isSubmittedTo.description: indicates the party to which something is submitted

reportsOn.name: reportsOn
reportsOn.description: indicates a subject matter, observation(s), assessment(s), focus or other topic of a report

submits.name: submits
submits.description: presents something (a proposal, application, report, or other document) for consideration or review

situates.name: situates
situates.description: indicates the place, setting, or context in which something is placed

appliesToAccount.name: appliesToAccount
appliesToAccount.description: indicates the account to which the transaction record or individual transaction applies

hasBalance.name: hasBalance
hasBalance.description: relates an account to the net amount of money available in that account

hasCloseDate.name: hasCloseDate
hasCloseDate.description: relates something to the date that it was closed

hasCorrespondingAccount.name: hasCorrespondingAccount
hasCorrespondingAccount.description: relates a credit agreement to an account used as the basis for managing transactions

hasEndingBalance.name: hasEndingBalance
hasEndingBalance.description: relates an account statement to the amount of money available in that account at the end of the statement period

hasOpenDate.name: hasOpenDate
hasOpenDate.description: relates something to the date that it was created

hasPaymentDueDate.name: hasPaymentDueDate
hasPaymentDueDate.description: indicates the date by which payment of some amount must be made to the creditor

hasPostingDate.name: hasPostingDate
hasPostingDate.description: indicates the date that the transaction was posted to the account

hasPrimaryAccountHolder.name: hasPrimaryAccountHolder
hasPrimaryAccountHolder.description: relates an account to a client or customer that is considered the primary owner of the account

hasSecondaryAccountHolder.name: hasSecondaryAccountHolder
hasSecondaryAccountHolder.description: relates an account to a client or customer that is considered a secondary, co-owner of the account

hasStartingBalance.name: hasStartingBalance
hasStartingBalance.description: relates an account statement to the amount of money available in that account at the beginning of the statement period

hasTransactionDate.name: hasTransactionDate
hasTransactionDate.description: indicates the date on which the transaction actually occurred

involvesMerchant.name: involvesMerchant
involvesMerchant.description: indicates the merchant (seller) involved in the transaction

isLinkedToAccount.name: isLinkedToAccount
isLinkedToAccount.description: connects a given customer account to another customer account

recordsTransaction.name: recordsTransaction
recordsTransaction.description: links an account statement to the individual transactions it documents

hasHomeCountry.name: hasHomeCountry
hasHomeCountry.description: indicates, with respect to a foreign bank, the country in which the foreign bank is chartered or incorporated

hasHomeCountrySupervisor.name: hasHomeCountrySupervisor
hasHomeCountrySupervisor.description: indicates, with respect to a foreign bank, the governmental entity or entities in the foreign bank's home country with responsibility for the supervision and regulation of the foreign bank

hasRating.name: hasRating
hasRating.description: indicates the rating assigned to a thing based on a grade or score according to a particular rating scale

hasRatingScore.name: hasRatingScore
hasRatingScore.description: indicates the grade or score associated with a rating with respect to a particular rating scale

producesRatingsFor.name: producesRatingsFor
producesRatingsFor.description: issuer for which ratings are produced or posted through

rates.name: rates
rates.description: indicates the instrument, party or something else to which a rating applies

usesRatingParty.name: usesRatingParty
usesRatingParty.description: rating performer an issuer uses to assess ratings

hasElectronicMailAddress.name: hasElectronicMailAddress
hasElectronicMailAddress.description: specifies an electronic messaging endpoint at which some entity may be located or contacted or may receive correspondence

hasTelephoneNumber.name: hasTelephoneNumber
hasTelephoneNumber.description: indicates a virtual address composed of a sequence of digits and symbols that may be assigned to a fixed-line telephone subscriber station, a wireless electronic telephony device, such as a radio telephone or a mobile telephone, or other similar device or service

hasUrbanization.name: hasUrbanization
hasUrbanization.description: indicates area, sector, or development within a geographic area relevant to a delivery address

hasCost.name: hasCost
hasCost.description: has amount payable for principal, interest, fees or other expenses

hasFirstRateChangeTerm.name: hasFirstRateChangeTerm
hasFirstRateChangeTerm.description: specifies a period of time in months after origination during which the interest rate cannot change

hasIndividualPayment.name: hasIndividualPayment
hasIndividualPayment.description: links an actual payment of principal, interest, and other related amounts to the overall payment history for an account

hasLoanBalance.name: hasLoanBalance
hasLoanBalance.description: indicates the balance with respect to the principal on the loan as of some date

hasPaymentHistory.name: hasPaymentHistory
hasPaymentHistory.description: relates a credit agreement, loan, or commitment to any history of payments that have been made by the borrower up to the point that payment history is requested

hasPrePaymentPenaltyTerm.name: hasPrePaymentPenaltyTerm
hasPrePaymentPenaltyTerm.description: relates a loan to a period of time in months after which there is no prepayment penalty

description._: indicates the nominal amount of the loan that must be paid at or before maturity

hasScheduledUnpaidBalance.name: hasScheduledUnpaidBalance
hasScheduledUnpaidBalance.description: indicates what the balance should be after a scheduled payment is made according to contract terms

hasTotalClosingCosts.name: hasTotalClosingCosts
hasTotalClosingCosts.description: indicates the total the amount paid at the closing of a real estate transaction, i.e., at the time when the title to the property is conveyed (transferred) to the buyer

hasTotalPointsAndFees.name: hasTotalPointsAndFees
hasTotalPointsAndFees.description: indicates a form of pre-paid interest, charged by the lender as an alternative to charging a higher rate of interest on the mortgage loan

isServicedBy.name: isServicedBy
isServicedBy.description: relates a loan to the financial service provider that services it

hasCardVerificationCode.name: hasCardVerificationCode
hasCardVerificationCode.description: links a credit card to either: (1) magnetic-stripe data, or (2) printed security features that are used to protect data integrity and limit alteration, counterfeiting and fraud generally

hasCreditCardNetwork.name: hasCreditCardNetwork
hasCreditCardNetwork.description: indicates the underlying network for credit card product

hasPrimaryAccountNumber.name: hasPrimaryAccountNumber
hasPrimaryAccountNumber.description: specifies the account number displayed on the face of the card

usesCurrency.name: usesCurrency
usesCurrency.description: indicates the currency defined for the credit card product

hasInitialFundingDate.name: hasInitialFundingDate
hasInitialFundingDate.description: relates a mortgage to the date on which the contract is consummated, officially creating the obligations therein

hasAssessmentBoundary.name: hasAssessmentBoundary
hasAssessmentBoundary.description: indicates the scope, limits, and context for an environmental or sustainability project

hasSpatialBoundary.name: hasSpatialBoundary
hasSpatialBoundary.description: specifies a geographic region included in an environmental or sustainability assessment, which may cover a specific site, facility, region, or the global operations of a company or project

description._: indicates the legal form that the fund takes
relates a pooled fund to a sub-fund that is a constituent of the parent fund
relates a pooled fund to a parent fund
links a depositary receipt to the instrument that it represents
links a depositary receipt to the instrument (equity or exchange-traded fund) that it represents

hasHoldingPeriod.name: hasHoldingPeriod
hasHoldingPeriod.description: identifies a holding period applicable to some financial asset

hasRestriction.name: hasRestriction
hasRestriction.description: identifies a restriction applicable to a given financial instrument or listing
